# Recovery-attempt input for LAMMPS reference bench (attempt_2+).
# Identical to upstream tests/apps/checkpointed/LAMMPS/bench/in.lj_restart
# but with `run upto 33000` instead of `run 10000`.
#
# Why: the upstream's `run 10000` runs an ADDITIONAL 10000 steps after
# restart, regardless of where attempt_1 stopped.  If attempt_1 ran
# 0->15000 (killed at 54s), attempt_2 then runs 15000->25000 — total
# 25000 steps vs the original 33000-step target.  This makes failure-
# injected wall-time SHORTER than failure-free (the LLM baseline runs
# all 33000 steps), which is the inverse of what a recovery measurement
# should show.
#
# `run N upto` is LAMMPS's absolute-target syntax: run until total step
# count reaches N.  See LAMMPS run command docs.
#
# attempt_1 input (in.lj_long, in patches/LAMMPS/bench/) writes
# restart.lj.<step> every 1000 steps via `restart 1000 restart.lj`.
# attempt_2 reads the highest-numbered file via the `*` glob.
read_restart    restart.lj.*

pair_style      lj/cut 2.5
pair_coeff      1 1 1.0 1.0 2.5

neighbor        0.3 bin
neigh_modify    delay 0 every 20 check no

fix             1 all nve

# Continue checkpoint
restart         1000 restart.lj

run             33000 upto
